EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT making a contingent appropriation for allocation to the
City of Reno for the restoration and refurbishment of the
Lear Theater in Reno, Nevada; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State
2 General Fund to the Interim Finance Committee the sum of
3 $12,500,000 for allocation to the City of Reno for the restoration
4 and refurbishment of the Lear Theater in Reno, Nevada, including,
5 without limitation, any necessary repairs to meet the requirements of
6 any applicable building, fire, health and safety codes.
7 2. Allocation of the money appropriated by subsection 1 is
8 contingent upon matching money being obtained by the City of
9 Reno, including, without limitation, gifts, grants and donations to
10 the City of Reno from private and public sources of money other
11 than the appropriation made by subsection 1. The Interim Finance
12 Committee shall not direct the transfer of any portion of money
13 from the appropriation made by subsection 1 until the City Manager
14 of the City of Reno submits to the Committee proof satisfactory to
15 the Committee that matching money in an equivalent amount has
16 been committed.
