1 3. Upon acceptance of the money appropriated by subsection 1,
2 the City Manager of the City of Reno agrees to:
3 (a) Prepare and transmit a report to the Interim Finance
4 Committee on or before December 18, 2026, that describes each
5 expenditure made from the money appropriated by subsection 1
6 from the date on which the money was received by the City of Reno
7 through December 1, 2026;
8 (b) Prepare and transmit a final report to the Interim Finance
9 Committee on or before September 17, 2027, that describes each
10 expenditure made from the money appropriated by subsection 1
11 from the date on which the money was received by the City of Reno
12 through June 30, 2027; and
13 (c) Upon request of the Legislative Commission, make available
14 to the Legislative Auditor any of the books, accounts, claims,
15 reports, vouchers or other records of information, confidential or
16 otherwise, of the City of Reno, regardless of their form or location,
17 that the Legislative Auditor deems necessary to conduct an audit of
18 the use of the money appropriated by subsection 1.
19 4. Any remaining balance of the appropriation made by
20 subsection 1 must not be committed for expenditure after June 30,
21 2027, by the entity to which the appropriation is made or any entity
22 to which money from the appropriation is granted or otherwise
23 transferred in any manner, and any portion of the appropriated
24 money remaining must not be spent for any purpose after
25 September 17, 2027, by either the entity to which the money was
26 appropriated or the entity to which the money was subsequently
27 granted or transferred, and must be reverted to the State General
28 Fund on or before September 17, 2027.
29 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.
